{"title_page": "Paulina Garc\u00eda", "text_new": "{{For|the Mexican television presenter, sportscaster and model|Paulina Garc\u00eda Robles}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Pali Garc\u00eda\n| image              = Paulina Garc\u00eda anfitriona Premios F\u00e9nix 2017 (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize          = 300px\n| caption            = Paulina Garc\u00eda, [[Berlin Film Festival Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]], [[63rd Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin, 2013]]\n| birthname          = Paulina Garc\u00eda Alfonso\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1960|11|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Santiago]], [[Chile]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 1983\u2013present\n| spouse             = Juan Carlos Zagal\n| children           = 3\n}}\n\n'''Paulina Garc\u00eda Alfonso''' (born 27 November 1960), better known as '''Pali Garc\u00eda''', is a [[Chile]]an  [[actor|actress]], [[theatre director]] and [[playwright]].\n\nGarc\u00eda debuted on television with a small role in the [[telenovela]] ''[[Los t\u00edteres]]'' (1984), but she was soon known for her theatre direction and for her various performances in films such as ''Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado'' (2002), ''Cachimba'' (2004), ''Casa de remolienda'' (2007) and ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'' (2013).\n\nGarc\u00eda has received four nominations for the [[Altazor Awards]], winning on one occasion, and three for the APES Awards \u2014 the Chilean Arts and Entertainment Critics Awards\u2014winning twice. In February, 2013 she won the prestigious [[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] for her performance in the movie ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'', directed by [[Sebasti\u00e1n Lelio]].<ref name=\"thisischile\" >[http://www.thisischile.cl/8506/2/chilean-paulina-garcia-wins-best-actress-at-berlin-film-fest/News.aspx Chilean Paulina Garc\u00eda wins best actress at Berlin Film Fest], ThisisChile.cl, 27 February 2013; retrieved 16 March 2013.</ref><ref name=\"latercera\" >[http://www.latercera.com/noticia/cultura/2013/02/1453-509368-9-paulina-garcia-gana-oso-de-plata-a-mejor-actriz-por-gloria-en-festival.shtml Paulina Garc\u00eda gana Oso de Plata a mejor actriz por \u201cGloria\u201d en Festival Internacional de Cine de Berl\u00edn], LaTercera.com, 16 February 2013; retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref> In 2016, she appeared in [[Ira Sachs]]' film, ''[[Little Men (2016 film)|Little Men]]''.\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Santiago]], Garc\u00eda studied [[Actor|acting]] at the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]], where she graduated with a degree in theatre arts and later with diplomas in theatre [[Theatre director|direction]] and [[Playwright|writing]].\n\nGarc\u00eda made her debut at Catholic University's theatre in 1983 in ''\u00bfD\u00f3nde estar\u00e1 la Jeanette?'' (\u201cWhere could Jeanette be?\u201d) by Luis Rivano, a work for which she received an APES Award for best actress. Since then, she has acted in over thirty productions including ''Cari\u00f1o malo'', by In\u00e9s Margarita Stranger, ''El t\u00edo Vania'', by [[Chekhov]], ''The Trojan Women'', by [[Euripides]], ''El lugar com\u00fan'', ''Las analfabetas'' and ''BBB-Up''.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/pali-garcia-de-pendenciera-a-emplumada/noticias/2008-10-05/172313.html Pali Garc\u00eda: De pendenciera a emplumada]. LaNaci\u00f3n.cl, 6 October 2008; retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref>\n\nThe year following her theatre debut, Garc\u00eda appeared on television as Adriana God\u00e1n in the TV series ''[[Los t\u00edteres]]'', a role she shared with actress [[Gloria M\u00fcnchmeyer]].<ref>[http://www.emol.com/noticias/magazine/2013/02/18/584593/gloria-munchmeyer-me-siento-orgullosa-de-haber-reconocido-el-talento-de-pali-garcia-desde-el-comienzo.html Gloria M\u00fcnchmeyer recuerda el d\u00eda en que Pali Garc\u00eda la impresion\u00f3 en la universidad]. El Mercurio. 18 February 2013. Retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref>\n\nThe first work she directed was ''El continente negro'' (\u201cThe Dark Continent\u201d) by Marco Antonio de la Parra for which she received an APES Award nomination for best director in 1996. A grant from the National Arts Development Fund (Fondo Nacional de Desarrollo Cultural de las Artes, [[FONDART]]) allowed for the financing of productions such as ''Lucrecia y Judith'' by the same author, and ''[[Look Back in Anger]]'' by [[John Osborne]]. She has also directed at national theatre festivals on three occasions, directing works by authors such as [[Alberto Fuguet]] and Celeste G\u00f3mez.\n\nGarc\u00eda has taught acting at the theatre school of the [[University of Chile]], at Fernando Gonz\u00e1lez night school, at the [[University for the Arts, Sciences, and Communication]] and the [[Universidad del Desarrollo|University for Development]]. Between 1997 and 2001, she founded and formed a part of the Theatre Directors Association (Asociaci\u00f3n de Directores de Teatro, ADT).\n\nIn television, of note is her performance in ''C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres'' (\u201cWomen\u2019s Prison\u201d) as Raquel,<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/gendarmeria-no-nos-permitio-conocer-su-realidad/noticias/2007-08-28/202318.html \u201cGendarmer\u00eda no nos permiti\u00f3 conocer su realidad\u201d]. La Naci\u00f3n. 29 August 2007. Retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref> a role for which Garc\u00eda received both an APES Award and the [[Altazor Awards|Altazor Award]] for best actress.<ref>[http://www.premioaltazor.cl/paulina-garcia-carcel-de-mujeres/ Paulina Garc\u00eda] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426064557/http://www.premioaltazor.cl/paulina-garcia-carcel-de-mujeres/ |date=2009-04-26 }}. Premioaltazor.cl. Retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Garc\u00eda received an Andes Foundation grant to undertake research on conjugal violence, ''Golpes extra\u00f1os al amor'' (\u201cBlows outside love\u201d), which led to the work ''Peso negro'' (\u201cDark weight\u201d), selected for the Unipersonales de Galp\u00f3n 7 Festival, and ''Fr\u00e1gil'' (\u201cFragile\u201d), a work presented at [[Centro Cultural Matucana 100|Matucana 100 Cultural Center]] under her direction.\n\nIn film, Garc\u00eda debuted in the 2002 movie ''[[Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado]]'' (\u201cThree nights of one Saturday\u201d) by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre, receiving a nomination for the [[Altazor Awards]] for her interpretation of the character Mathilde. She also appeared in the 2004 film ''[[Cachimba (film)|Cachimba]]'' (\u201cHookah\u201d) by Silvio Caiozzi, in ''[[Casa de remolienda]]'' (\u201cParty house\u201d) by Eyzaguirre in 2007,<ref name=\"emol\">[http://www.emol.com/noticias/magazine/2007/08/29/273668/director-de-casa-de-remolienda-lo-folklorico-es-bonito-pero-para-los-museos.html Director de \"Casa de Remolienda\": Lo folkl\u00f3rico es bonito, pero para los museos]. El Mercurio. 29 August 2007. Retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref> and in ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'', by [[Sebasti\u00e1n Lelio]], for which she received the [[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"thisischile\"/><ref name=\"latercera\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado]]'' \n| Mathilde\n| Directed by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre<br>Nominated\u2014[[Altazor Awards|Altazor Awards Best Actress for Cinema]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2004\n| ''[[Cachimba (film)|Cachimba]]''\n| Antoinette Doubl\u00e9\n| Directed by [[Silvio Caiozzi]]\n|-\n| ''[[M\u00f3nica, vida m\u00eda]]''\n| Noem\u00ed\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Casa de remolienda]]''<ref name=\"emol\" />\n| Do\u00f1a Rebeca\n| Directed by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| ''[[Bah\u00eda azul]]''\n| \n| Directed by Nicol\u00e1s Acu\u00f1a\n|-\n| ''[[El muro (pel\u00edcula)]]''\n| Former Minister for Culture\n| Directed by Paula Bravo\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2013\n| ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]''\n| Gloria Cumplido\n| Directed by [[Sebasti\u00e1n Lelio]]<br>[[Altazor Awards|Altazor Award for Best Actress]]<br>[[Silver Bear for Best Actress|Silver Bear for Best Actress at the Berlin International Film Festival]]<br>[[Hawaii International Film Festival|Hawaii International Film Festival Award for Best Actress]]<br>Pedro Sienna Award for Best Actress<br>Nominated&ndash;[[The Guardian|Guardian Film Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| ''[[Illiterate (film)|Illiterate]]''\n| Ximena\n| Directed by Mois\u00e9s Sep\u00falveda<br>Kikito for Best Actress at the Festival de Cinema de Gramado - Brazil\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Voice Over (film)|Voice Over]]''\n| Matilda\n| Directed by [[Cristi\u00e1n Jim\u00e9nez]]\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The 33 (film)|The 33]]''\n| Isabel Pereira, assistant to President Pi\u00f1era\n| Directed by [[Patricia Riggen]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| ''[[Aqu\u00ed no ha pasado nada]]''\n| Roxana\n| Directed by [[Alejandro Fern\u00e1ndez Almendras]]\n|-\n| ''[[Little Men (2016 film)|Little Men]]''\n| Leonor Calvelli\n| Directed by [[Ira Sachs]]<br>Nominated &ndash; [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Supporting Female]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2017\n| ''[[The Desert Bride (2017 film)|The Desert Bride]]''\n| Teresa Godoy\n| Directed by [[Cecilia At\u00e1n]] and [[Valeria Pivato]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Summit (2017 film)|The Summit ]]''\n| Paula Sherson, President of Chile\n| Directed by [[Santiago Mitre]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| ''[[Blood Will Tell (2019 film)|Blood Will Tell ]]''\n| Adriana, the mother\n| Directed by Miguel Cohan\n|-\n| ''[[Some Beasts]]''\n| Dolores\n| Directed by Jorge Riquelme Serrano\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year !!Title!!Role!!Notes\n|-\n|1984 ||''[[Los t\u00edteres]]'' ||Adriana God\u00e1n ||\n|-\n|1986 ||''[[La villa (telenovela)|La villa]]'' ||Eliana \"Eli\" ||\n|-\n|1987 ||''[[La invitaci\u00f3n (telenovela)|La invitaci\u00f3n]]'' ||Laura del Solar ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1989 ||''[[A la sombra del \u00e1ngel]]'' ||Edith ||\n|-\n|''[[Los Venegas]]'' ||Jefa de Guillermo ||Televised series (Season 1)\n|-\n|1990 ||''[[El milagro de vivir]]'' ||Mar\u00eda P\u00eda Santill\u00e1n ||\n|-\n|2003 ||''[[JPT: Justicia Para Todos]]'' ||Catalina ||Episode: \"Tr\u00e1fico de \u00f3rganos\" (Season 2)\n|-\n|2006 ||''[[Huaiquim\u00e1n y Tolosa]]'' ||Do\u00f1a Berta ||Episode: \"\u00bfLa mafia rusa?\" (Season 1)\n|-\n|2007 ||''[[H\u00e9roes (Chilean miniseries)|H\u00e9roes]]'' ||Mar\u00eda Encarnaci\u00f3n de Fern\u00e1ndez y Palazuelos ||Episode: \"[[H\u00e9roes (Chilean miniseries)#\"Portales.2C la fuerza de los hechos\"|Portales, la fuerza de los hechos]]\"\n|-\n|2007\u201308 ||''[[C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres (Chilean television series)|C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres]]'' ||Raquel \"La Raco\" Reina ||'''Winner'''\u2014[[Altazor Awards]]\n|-\n|2010 ||''[[Los simuladores (Chile television series)|Los simuladores]]'' ||Marcela ||Episode: \"El secreto de Marcela\" (Season 2)\n|-\n|2011 ||''[[Los archivos del cardenal]]'' ||M\u00f3nica Spencer ||\n|-\n|2015 ||''[[Narcos]]'' ||Hermilda Gaviria||\n|}\n\n==Theatre==\n\n=== Actress ===\n* ''\u00bfD\u00f3nde estar\u00e1 la Jeanette?'', comedy by Luis Rivano\n* ''Cari\u00f1o malo'', by In\u00e9s Stranger; dir.: Claudia Echenique; 1990; 2012\n* ''Malasangre'', dir.: Mauricio Celed\u00f3n, 1991\n* ''El t\u00edo Vania'', by [[Anton Chekhov]]; dir.: Ra\u00fal Osorio, 1994\n* ''El lugar com\u00fan''\n* ''Inocencia'', by Dea Loher; dir.: Luis Ureta; Muestra de Dramaturgia Europea, 2004\n* ''En la Sangre'', by Suzan-Lori Parks; dir.: Carlos Osorio; interprets Hester, a beggar; Centro Cultural Matucana 100, 2004\n* ''D\u00e9jala sangrar'', by Benjam\u00edn Galemiri, dir.: Adel Hakim; interprets Virna Vigo; 2005\n* ''El \u00faltimo fuego'', by Dea Loer; dir.: Luis Ureta; April 2009\n* ''Gertrudis, el grito'', by Howard Barker, dir.: Marcos Guzm\u00e1n; 9th Festival of Contemporary European Theatre in Santiago, August 2009\n* ''Las analfabetas'', by Pablo Paredes, 2010\n* ''F\u00e1bula del ni\u00f1o y los animales que se mueren'', free version of [[Euripides]] ''The Trojan Women'' by Pablo Paredes; dir.: Isidora Stevenson; Garc\u00eda interprets queen Hecuba; La Nacional company in [[Centro Cultural Matucana 100|Matucana 100]], 6\u201315 January 2012\n\n=== Director ===\n* ''El continente negro'', by [[Marco Antonio de la Parra]]; 1996\n* ''Lucrecia y Judith'', by Marco Antonio de la Parra\n* ''Recordando con ira'', by [[John Osborne]] ([[Look Back in Anger]] in English)\n* ''Anhelo del coraz\u00f3n'', by [[Caryl Churchill]] (\u201cA Heart\u2019s Desire\u201d); Muestra de Dramaturgia Europea, 2004\n* ''El neoproceso'', work by Benjam\u00edn Galemiri inspired by [[Kafka]], premiere: 15 July 2006\n* ''La gran noche'', by Marcelo Simonetti; premiere: 28 May 2008, [[Centro Mori]] in [[Vitacura]]\n* ''Apoteosis final: BBB up'', Santiago a Mil, January 2009\n* ''Orates'', by Jaime Lorca; premiere: 4 November 2010\n* ''La mantis religiosa'', by [[Alejandro Sieveking]], La Palomera theatre, premiere: 9 June 2011\n* ''Cerca de Mosc\u00fa'', adaptation by Pablo Paredes of two pieces by Chekhov: ''Platonov'' and ''Ivanov''; Santiago a Mil International Festival 2013<ref>[http://www.latercera.com/noticia/cultura/2013/03/1453-512648-9-montaje-dirigido-por-actriz-ganadora-del-oso-de-plata-se-presentara-nuevamente.shtml Montaje dirigido por actriz ganadora del Oso de Plata se presentar\u00e1 nuevamente en Santiago]. La Tercera. 8 March 2013. Retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref>\n\n===Playwright===\n* ''Peso negro''\n* ''Fr\u00e1gil'', 2002; premiered and directed by Garc\u00eda in 2003.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===APES Award===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result\n|-\n| 1983 || Best Actress ||Theatre || ''\u00bfD\u00f3nde estar\u00e1 la Jeanette?'' ||{{won}}\n|-\n| 1996 || Best Director ||Theatre|| ''El continente negro'' ||{{nom}}\n|-\n| 2008 || Best Actress ||Television || ''[[C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres (TV series)|C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres]]'' ||{{won}}\n|}\n\n=== Altazor Awards ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result\n|-\n| 2003 || Best Actress ||Film || ''Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado'' ||{{nom}}\n|-\n| 2005 || Best Actress ||Theatre|| ''En la Sangre'' ||{{won}}\n|-\n| 2008 || Best Actress ||Television || ''[[C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres (serie de TV)|C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres]]''  ||{{won}}\n|-\n| 2009 || Best Actress ||Television|| ''[[C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres (serie de TV)|C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres 2]]''  || {{nom}}\n|}\n\n===Silver Bear for Best Actress===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result\n|-\n| 2013 ||[[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] ||Film\n|| ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'' ||{{won}}\n|}\n\n=== Platino Awards ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result\n|-\n| 2014 || Best Actress ||Film || ''Gloria'' ||{{won}}\n|}\n\n== Festival de Cinema de Gramado - Brazil ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Work !! Result\n|-\n| 2014 || Kikito for Best Actress ||Film || ''[[Illiterate (film)|Illiterate]]'' ||{{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Paulina Garc\u00eda\n|list  = \n{{Silver Bear for Best Actress}}\n{{Platino Award for Best Actress}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia, Paulina}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Santiago]]\n[[Category:Chilean film actresses]]\n[[Category:Chilean stage actresses]]\n[[Category:Chilean telenovela actresses]]\n[[Category:Chilean television actresses]]\n[[Category:Chilean dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Chilean theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Silver Bear for Best Actress winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the Mexican television presenter, sportscaster and model|Paulina Garc\u00eda Robles}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Pali Garc\u00eda\n| image              = Paulina Garc\u00eda anfitriona Premios F\u00e9nix 2017 (cropped).jpg\n| imagesize          = 300px\n| caption            = Paulina Garc\u00eda, [[Berlin Film Festival Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]], [[63rd Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin, 2013]]\n| birthname          = Paulina Garc\u00eda Alfonso\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1960|11|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Santiago]], [[Chile]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 1983\u2013present\n| spouse             = Juan Carlos Zagal\n| children           = 3\n}}\n\n'''Paulina Garc\u00eda Alfonso''' (born 27 November 1960), better known as '''Pali Garc\u00eda''', is a [[Chile]]an  [[actor|actress]], [[theatre director]] and [[playwright]].\n\nGarc\u00eda debuted on television with a small role in the [[telenovela]] ''[[Los t\u00edteres]]'' (1984), but she was soon known for her theatre direction and for her various performances in films such as ''Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado'' (2002), ''Cachimba'' (2004), ''Casa de remolienda'' (2007) and ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'' (2013).\n\nGarc\u00eda has received four nominations for the [[Altazor Awards]], winning on one occasion, and three for the APES Awards \u2014 the Chilean Arts and Entertainment Critics Awards\u2014winning twice. In February, 2013 she won the prestigious [[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] for her performance in the movie ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'', directed by [[Sebasti\u00e1n Lelio]].<ref name=\"thisischile\" >[http://www.thisischile.cl/8506/2/chilean-paulina-garcia-wins-best-actress-at-berlin-film-fest/News.aspx Chilean Paulina Garc\u00eda wins best actress at Berlin Film Fest], ThisisChile.cl, 27 February 2013; retrieved 16 March 2013.</ref><ref name=\"latercera\" >[http://www.latercera.com/noticia/cultura/2013/02/1453-509368-9-paulina-garcia-gana-oso-de-plata-a-mejor-actriz-por-gloria-en-festival.shtml Paulina Garc\u00eda gana Oso de Plata a mejor actriz por \u201cGloria\u201d en Festival Internacional de Cine de Berl\u00edn], LaTercera.com, 16 February 2013; retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref> In 2016, she appeared in [[Ira Sachs]]' film, ''[[Little Men (2016 film)|Little Men]]''.\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Santiago]], Garc\u00eda studied [[Actor|acting]] at the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]], where she graduated with a degree in theatre arts and later with diplomas in theatre [[Theatre director|direction]] and [[Playwright|writing]].\n\nGarc\u00eda made her debut at Catholic University's theatre in 1983 in ''\u00bfD\u00f3nde estar\u00e1 la Jeanette?'' (\u201cWhere could Jeanette be?\u201d) by Luis Rivano, a work for which she received an APES Award for best actress. Since then, she has acted in over thirty productions including ''Cari\u00f1o malo'', by In\u00e9s Margarita Stranger, ''El t\u00edo Vania'', by [[Chekhov]], ''The Trojan Women'', by [[Euripides]], ''El lugar com\u00fan'', ''Las analfabetas'' and ''BBB-Up''.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/pali-garcia-de-pendenciera-a-emplumada/noticias/2008-10-05/172313.html Pali Garc\u00eda: De pendenciera a emplumada]. LaNaci\u00f3n.cl, 6 October 2008; retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref>\n\nThe year following her theatre debut, Garc\u00eda appeared on television as Adriana God\u00e1n in the TV series ''[[Los t\u00edteres]]'', a role she shared with actress [[Gloria M\u00fcnchmeyer]].<ref>[http://www.emol.com/noticias/magazine/2013/02/18/584593/gloria-munchmeyer-me-siento-orgullosa-de-haber-reconocido-el-talento-de-pali-garcia-desde-el-comienzo.html Gloria M\u00fcnchmeyer recuerda el d\u00eda en que Pali Garc\u00eda la impresion\u00f3 en la universidad]. El Mercurio. 18 February 2013. Retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref>\n\nThe first work she directed was ''El continente negro'' (\u201cThe Dark Continent\u201d) by Marco Antonio de la Parra for which she received an APES Award nomination for best director in 1996. A grant from the National Arts Development Fund (Fondo Nacional de Desarrollo Cultural de las Artes, [[FONDART]]) allowed for the financing of productions such as ''Lucrecia y Judith'' by the same author, and ''[[Look Back in Anger]]'' by [[John Osborne]]. She has also directed at national theatre festivals on three occasions, directing works by authors such as [[Alberto Fuguet]] and Celeste G\u00f3mez.\n\nGarc\u00eda has taught acting at the theatre school of the [[University of Chile]], at Fernando Gonz\u00e1lez night school, at the [[University for the Arts, Sciences, and Communication]] and the [[Universidad del Desarrollo|University for Development]]. Between 1997 and 2001, she founded and formed a part of the Theatre Directors Association (Asociaci\u00f3n de Directores de Teatro, ADT).\n\nIn television, of note is her performance in ''C\u00e1rcel de Mujeres'' (\u201cWomen\u2019s Prison\u201d) as Raquel,<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/gendarmeria-no-nos-permitio-conocer-su-realidad/noticias/2007-08-28/202318.html \u201cGendarmer\u00eda no nos permiti\u00f3 conocer su realidad\u201d]. La Naci\u00f3n. 29 August 2007. Retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref> a role for which Garc\u00eda received both an APES Award and the [[Altazor Awards|Altazor Award]] for best actress.<ref>[http://www.premioaltazor.cl/paulina-garcia-carcel-de-mujeres/ Paulina Garc\u00eda] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426064557/http://www.premioaltazor.cl/paulina-garcia-carcel-de-mujeres/ |date=2009-04-26 }}. Premioaltazor.cl. Retrieved 2 April 2013.</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Garc\u00eda received an Andes Foundation grant to undertake research on conjugal violence, ''Golpes extra\u00f1os al amor'' (\u201cBlows outside love\u201d), which led to the work ''Peso negro'' (\u201cDark weight\u201d), selected for the Unipersonales de Galp\u00f3n 7 Festival, and ''Fr\u00e1gil'' (\u201cFragile\u201d), a work presented at [[Centro Cultural Matucana 100|Matucana 100 Cultural Center]] under her direction.\n\nIn film, Garc\u00eda debuted in the 2002 movie ''[[Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado]]'' (\u201cThree nights of one Saturday\u201d) by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre, receiving a nomination for the [[Altazor Awards]] for her interpretation of the character Mathilde. She also appeared in the 2004 film ''[[Cachimba (film)|Cachimba]]'' (\u201cHookah\u201d) by Silvio Caiozzi, in ''[[Casa de remolienda]]'' (\u201cParty house\u201d) by Eyzaguirre in 2007,<ref name=\"emol\">[http://www.emol.com/noticias/magazine/2007/08/29/273668/director-de-casa-de-remolienda-lo-folklorico-es-bonito-pero-para-los-museos.html Director de \"Casa de Remolienda\": Lo folkl\u00f3rico es bonito, pero para los museos]. El Mercurio. 29 August 2007. Retrieved 1 April 2013.</ref> and in ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]]'', by [[Sebasti\u00e1n Lelio]], for which she received the [[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"thisischile\"/><ref name=\"latercera\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Tres noches de un s\u00e1bado]]'' \n| Mathilde\n| Directed by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre<br>Nominated\u2014[[Altazor Awards|Altazor Awards Best Actress for Cinema]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2004\n| ''[[Cachimba (film)|Cachimba]]''\n| Antoinette Doubl\u00e9\n| Directed by [[Silvio Caiozzi]]\n|-\n| ''[[M\u00f3nica, vida m\u00eda]]''\n| Noem\u00ed\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Casa de remolienda]]''<ref name=\"emol\" />\n| Do\u00f1a Rebeca\n| Directed by Joaqu\u00edn Eyzaguirre\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| ''[[Bah\u00eda azul]]''\n| \n| Directed by Nicol\u00e1s Acu\u00f1a\n|-\n| ''[[El muro (pel\u00edcula)]]''\n| Former Minister for Culture\n| Directed by Paula Bravo\n|-